member.summary:
/// The user can set some tolerance or threshold limits inorder to take appropriate actions when
 their transactions are above or below certain threshold limits.
 Account Payable (AP) status code indicates an action that needs to be taken when the tolerance/threshold falls between certain range.

An exemption reason defines why a certificate allows a customer to be exempt
for purposes of tax calculation. For a full list of defined exemption reasons,
please call the `ListCertificateExemptionReasons` API.

The unique ID number of the tax code that is applied when selling this item.
When creating or updating an item, you can either specify the Tax Code ID number or the Tax Code string;
you do not need to specify both values.

The unique code string of the Tax Code that is applied when selling this item.
When creating or updating an item, you can either specify the Tax Code ID number or the Tax Code string;
you do not need to specify both values.
